trans-unit.source: Physical memory is one-dimensional; strides provide a mechanism to map a given index to an address in memory. For an N-dimensional array, its strides attribute is an N-element tuple; advancing from index i to index i+1 on axis n means adding a.strides[n] bytes to the address.
trans-unit.target: 物理内存是一维的；跨步提供了一种机制，可以将给定索引映射到内存中的地址。对于一个N维数组，其 strides 属性是一个N元组。在轴 n 上从索引 i 前进到索引 i+1 意味着向地址添加 a.strides[n] 个字节。

trans-unit.source: Prior to numpy 1.13, the behaviour of ufuncs could only be tuned using __array_wrap__ and __array_prepare__. These two allowed one to change the output type of a ufunc, but, in contrast to __array_ufunc__, did not allow one to make any changes to the inputs. It is hoped to eventually deprecate these, but __array_wrap__ is also used by other numpy functions and methods, such as squeeze, so at the present time is still needed for full functionality.
trans-unit.target: 此前numpy的1.13，ufuncs的行为只能通过调整 __array_wrap__ 和 __array_prepare__ 。这两个允许一个更改ufunc的输出类型，但是与 __array_ufunc__ 相反，不允许一个对输入进行任何更改。希望最终不要使用它们，但是 __array_wrap__ 也被其他numpy函数和方法（例如 squeeze )使用，因此，目前仍需要完整的功能。

trans-unit.source: Provides a policy for what kind of casting is permitted. For compatibility with previous versions of NumPy, this defaults to ‘unsafe’ for numpy < 1.7. In numpy 1.7 a transition to ‘same_kind’ was begun where ufuncs produce a DeprecationWarning for calls which are allowed under the ‘unsafe’ rules, but not under the ‘same_kind’ rules. From numpy 1.10 and onwards, the default is ‘same_kind’.
trans-unit.target: 提供允许使用哪种类型的转换的政策。为了与NumPy的早期版本兼容，对于numpy <1.7，默认情况下为“不安全”。在numpy 1.7中，开始向“ same_kind”的过渡，其中ufunc会为“不安全”规则（而非“ same_kind”规则）允许的调用生成DeprecationWarning。从numpy 1.10起，默认值为'same_kind'。
